                <div id="bloco-txt-lesma-mesma">
                    <h2>Lesma Mesma</h2>
                    <p>Lesma Mesma vivia sua vidinha de lesma. Andava como uma lesma, comia como uma lesma, até o dia que ela ouve a seguinte pergunta: o que tem de tão fabuloso em sua vida?<br /><br />O livro é uma fábula poética para ler e reler devagar, a divagar, bem no estilo da Lesma Edições.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="sobre-lesma" class="content">
                <div id="bloco-txt-sobre-lesma">
                    <h2>Lesma Edições</h2>
                    <p>In Portuguese, "lesma" means "snail" and "lema" translates as "slogan". Therefore, the “slowgan” of Lesma Edições is: We publish slowly, slowly roaming.<br /><br />To date, there are only two books listed in our catalogue. That is why there's no need for you to enlist with us, log in or categorize them.<br /><br />Take your time to look at the logo and the website of Lesma Edições, which still features few news entries. There is no hurry, therefore, to scan it as quickly as you can. Slow down. If you don't, if you're too fast, you might come to think that we don't have anything to offer. We can only remind you again and again: take your time, go slowly. A good read can sometimes be like that. Wondering about a few thoughts, wandering about the book, your mind, the world. <br /><br /><br />No, you don't have to be slow with us, we don't want everybody to be slow. We're not starting a club in which all members have to think equally and walk at the same pace. But it is always an invitation worth considering to stop for a while, read a book and enjoy the world around you. <br /><br />And this is what we would like to invite you to do. Take a look at our work and, if you become interested in reading some of our publications, feel free to open our books. Our mascot is like that, too: a snail which roams freely and slowly about the world, leaving its marks everywhere it passes on its journey. <br /><br />We are only starting out, discovering who we are. The idea of becoming an editor is a new one. Therefore, we still don't have a definite way of presenting our work. <br /><br />Easy to do? No, it is never easy to find the simple things, but we keep trying. May it be a good start.<br /><br /><b>The team of Lesma Edições</b></p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="sobre-selma" class="content">
                <figure>
                    <img src="@Url.Content("~/Content/images/image-bio-selma.jpg")" title="Selma Maria" />
                </figure>

                <div id="bloco-txt-selma">
                    <h2>Selma Maria</h2>
                    <p>Born in São Paulo (Brazil) in 1965, she is a multi-artist, working as an writer, visual artist and researching childhood. She travels through the interior of her native country, Brazil, visiting villages and towns in search of words and toys that may be found in the drawers of imagination.</p>
                    <h2>She featured in the following exhibitions:</h2>
                    <p>Meninos Quietos (Quiet children) - a look on the toys of the Brazilian interior;<br />Mundo Livro (Book world), As palavras e o mundo (Words and the world);<br />Trilhas do Brincar (The tracks of playing);<br />Infâncias (Childhoods);<br />Lá e Cá: os livros viajantes (Here and there: travelling books);<br />Brasil 12 x 12 Alemanha (Brazil 12 x 12 Germany)</p>
                    <h2>Livros</h2>
                    <p>Um pequeno tratado de brinquedos para meninos quietos (A small treaty of toys for quiet children);<br />Um pequeno tratado de brinquedos para meninos quietos da cidade (A small treaty of toys for quiet children of the city);<br />Isso Isso (This this);<br />O último livro de papel (The last paper book) — Peirópolis publishers<br />Superímã e o mar (Super magnet and the sea); A menina que nunca terminava nada (The girl who never finished anything) — published by Sesi-SP publishers Ora Bolas! — Tordesilhinhas publishers ABC da água (Water ABC) — Guia dos Curiosos Communications
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

